The Bank of England said it provided themarket with a further 570 mln stg assistance during the morningafter revising its estimate of the liquidity shortage to 1.85billion stg, before taking account of its early round of billpurchases.    Initially, the Bank put the likely shortage at some 1.75billion and to help offset this gave early assistance of 1.143billion.    Its total help so far today amounts to 1.713 billion stg. MORE&#3;